  "Allegations" : "FINRA RULES 2010, 8210, NASD RULES 2110, 3030, 3040:  LIBMAN OBTAINED A CHECK IN THE AMOUNT OF $202,673.58 FROM A FRIEND, MAKING THE CHECK PAYABLE TO HERSELF AND ENDORSED IT TO LIBMAN. LIBMAN DEPOSITED THE CHECK INTO HIS PERSONAL CHECKING ACCOUNT. LIBMAN WITHDREW $200,000 OF THE FUNDS AND INVESTED THE FUNDS IN A PRIVATE SECURITIES TRANSACTION PURSUANT TO A PARTICIPATION AGREEMENT WITH A COMPANY. LIBMAN RECEIVED COMPENSATION FROM THE COMPANY AS A RESULT OF THE PRIVATE SECURITIES TRANSACTION. LIBMAN FAILED TO NOTIFY THE FIRM IN WRITING, AND OBTAIN ITS PRIOR APPROVAL PRIOR TO MAKING THE INVESTMENT. THE AGREEMENT WITH THE COMPANY WAS AN OUTSIDE BUSINESS ACTIVITY FOR LIBMAN AND HE RECEIVED COMPENSATION AS A RESULT OF THE AGREEMENT. LIBMAN DID NOT PROVIDE ANY NOTICE TO HIS MEMBER FIRM ABOUT THE OUTSIDE BUSINESS ACTIVITY. FOLLOWING THE COMPANY'S COLLAPSE, THE FIRM SENT A QUESTIONNAIRE TO ITS BROKERS ASKING WHETHER THEY INVESTED THEIR OWN FUNDS IN THE COMPANY, REFERRED ANY INDIVIDUAL TO THE COMPANY, ADVISED ANYONE TO INVEST IN THE COMPANY, OR FACILITATED ANY INVESTMENT INTO THE COMPANY. LIBMAN'S RESPONSE TO THE FIRM'S QUESTIONNAIRE WAS FALSE BECAUSE HE STATED HE USED PERSONAL MONEY TO INVEST; HE DID NOT INVEST HIS OWN FUNDS; INSTEAD, HE INVESTED THOSE OF HIS FRIEND. FURTHER, LIBMAN'S RESPONSE WAS MISLEADING BECAUSE IT FAILED TO ADDRESS WHETHER HE REFERRED ANYONE TO THE COMPANY, ADVISED ANYONE TO INVEST IN COMPANY, OR FACILITATED ANY INVESTMENT INTO COMPANY. LIBMAN PROVIDED FALSE TESTIMONY TO FINRA AND REFUSED TO PROVIDE COMPLETE INFORMATION AND DOCUMENTS TO FINRA. LIBMAN'S COUNSEL ALSO INFORMED FINRA THAT LIBMAN WOULD NO LONGER COOPERATE WITH ITS INVESTIGATION.",
